AnimateDiff-Vid2Anime Workflow (Free Version)

Here are some steps to run this workflow. Follow along you will be no problem :)

1- Load Vdeo group
- Input your video file path.
- Set Width and Height
- Set Frame cap , this is not number of seconds or the FPS in the video

2- SEG Mask Group
The only thing you need to do in this group , the Segment Prompt - prompt and threshold

3- Loader Group
Basically, select your checkpoint model. If you are using LCM checkpoint model, then Bypass the LCM - Load Lora node. Otherwise if you are using non-LCM checkpoint model and you want to laverage LCM for generation speed, then turn it on.
Text Prompt - change color , background envoirment whatever you can think of.

4-AnimateDiff Prepare Group
Nothing much you need to set, just choose the motion model, and select the right scheduler.
Lastly, wait for the generate result and have fun! :)
